163
00:13:37,390 --> 00:13:39,160
  Let's create a suspect.

164
00:13:39,160 --> 00:13:41,270

Someone in his thirties whom we won't be able to identify.

165
00:13:41,270 --> 00:13:44,370
 Male. We need a body.

166
00:13:44,370 --> 00:13:47,460
 I know a guy who takes care of that stuff.

167
00:13:47,460 --> 00:13:53,340
 In return, this is the last deal we make.

168
00:13:54,770 --> 00:13:57,250

169
00:14:24,060 --> 00:14:26,950

170
00:14:28,610 --> 00:14:30,110
 Code zero. Code zero.

171
00:14:30,110 --> 00:14:32,270
 A patient from Yooseong Mental Hospital has escaped.

172
00:14:32,270 --> 00:14:34,610
 I repeat, a patient from Yooseong Mental Hospital has escaped.

173
00:14:34,610 --> 00:14:36,380
You'll need to take measures.

174
00:14:36,380 --> 00:14:40,460
Eom Soo Tak, who escaped from the hospital, is connected to that bastard.

175
00:14:41,270 --> 00:14:44,490
We need the local police, not Mucheon Metropolitan Police Agency,

176
00:14:44,490 --> 00:14:46,210
to catch him quietly.

177
00:14:46,210 --> 00:14:51,580
Okay. I'll let the station in the hospital's vicinity know.

178
00:14:51,580 --> 00:14:54,000
Okay, I got it.

179
00:15:03,290 --> 00:15:05,290

180
00:15:06,170 --> 00:15:09,770
 4789 is a patient named Eom Soo Tak.

181
00:15:09,770 --> 00:15:11,620
Five years ago, Ha Tae Sik asked him to

182
00:15:11,620 --> 00:15:15,180
put a fake corpse at the Joonggeon three-way intersection in place of that bastard.

183
00:15:15,180 --> 00:15:17,740
 He was kidnapped by that bastard and ran away,

184
00:15:17,740 --> 00:15:20,190
 and Ha Tae Sik hid him here.

185
00:15:20,190 --> 00:15:24,430
That bastard let Eom Soo Tak go on purpose.

186
00:15:24,430 --> 00:15:27,170
That sounds like you are saying that you can catch that bastard.

187
00:15:27,170 --> 00:15:30,610
Eom Soo Tak fled. Hurry.

188
00:15:30,610 --> 00:15:33,440
That bastard will definitely look for Eom Soo Tak.

189
00:15:33,440 --> 00:15:36,670
We'll find him. I'll call you later.

190
00:15:37,890 --> 00:15:42,070

191
00:15:43,800 --> 00:15:46,780
4789 was Ha Tae Sik's minion.

192
00:15:46,780 --> 00:15:50,220
Even though he ran away, he couldn't have gone far. We have to find him.

193
00:15:50,220 --> 00:15:52,820
I'll keep an eye on Oh Hyeon Jae.

194
00:15:52,820 --> 00:15:55,310
He's not the kind of person who would lose him from his grasp.

195
00:15:55,310 --> 00:15:58,310
I'm sure he has a plan.

196
00:15:58,310 --> 00:16:01,240
But one thing is certain.

197
00:16:01,240 --> 00:16:05,060
That the information you gave me was right.

198
00:16:05,060 --> 00:16:07,550
What is it that you really want?

199
00:16:09,530 --> 00:16:13,410
When we catch that bastard, under the guise of emergency,

200
00:16:13,410 --> 00:16:15,550
I'll use my discretion.

201
00:16:15,550 --> 00:16:19,550
What do you mean? That you'll shoot?

202
00:16:19,550 --> 00:16:21,810
Perhaps, is it because you want to kill that bastard with your own hands...

203
00:16:21,810 --> 00:16:25,540
Let's say that that's how much I want to catch him.

204
00:16:27,680 --> 00:16:31,740
Now, please give me the information that you have.

205
00:16:32,740 --> 00:16:36,550
Not yet. Let's wait and see.

206
00:16:57,570 --> 00:17:00,260
- Where is it? 
 - Over there.

207
00:17:01,050 --> 00:17:04,160
Over there.

208
00:17:07,310 --> 00:17:11,910
In this little village, this is the second suicide already.

209
00:17:11,910 --> 00:17:14,880
Hey, it's different this time.

210
00:17:14,880 --> 00:17:17,310
It's Section Chief Bang.

211
00:17:17,310 --> 00:17:19,550
What in the world is going on here?

212
00:17:19,550 --> 00:17:21,420
I know.

213
00:17:22,520 --> 00:17:24,820
This is another suicide.

214
00:17:28,740 --> 00:17:30,280
I hear he had a lot of gambling debt.

215
00:17:30,280 --> 00:17:32,350
There are rumors about him getting private loans.

216
00:17:32,350 --> 00:17:34,960
What? Someone else died in a matter of days?

217
00:17:34,960 --> 00:17:37,110
It's that man!

218
00:17:37,110 --> 00:17:40,330
- You don't know anything? 
 - Not much yet.

219
00:17:40,330 --> 00:17:43,030
Right? I told you.

220
00:17:49,790 --> 00:17:52,890
Give me the last caller's number.

221
00:18:04,510 --> 00:18:08,240
What is this atmosphere that's like the quiet in the middle of a typhoon?

222
00:18:08,240 --> 00:18:10,590
What do you mean a typhoon?

223
00:18:10,590 --> 00:18:13,700
It's too quiet.

224
00:18:17,950 --> 00:18:19,580
Hello, it's Cha Soo Yeong.

225
00:18:19,580 --> 00:18:21,690
 I'm Detective Kim Woo Sik at Hwayeong Police Station.

226
00:18:21,690 --> 00:18:24,850
 By chance, do you know Detective Bang Sang Sik?

227
00:18:24,850 --> 00:18:26,440
Yes, I do.

228
00:18:26,440 --> 00:18:28,330

229
00:18:29,530 --> 00:18:31,750
Have some coffee.

230
00:18:31,750 --> 00:18:33,640
Thank you.

231
00:18:33,640 --> 00:18:35,970
You're a Metropolitan Investigation Unit detective?

232
00:18:35,970 --> 00:18:37,800
Yes.

233
00:18:37,800 --> 00:18:40,510
What is the cause of death?

234
00:18:40,510 --> 00:18:45,000
He committed suicide. A hiker found him a short while ago.

235
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:48,000
He hung himself on a tree.

236
00:18:49,240 --> 00:18:52,140
You called him many times yesterday.

237
00:18:52,140 --> 00:18:56,120
Oh... yes. We only got to speak once.

238
00:18:56,120 --> 00:19:00,070
I had something personal to ask him.

239
00:19:00,070 --> 00:19:04,290
But he called me back at night.

240
00:19:11,210 --> 00:19:13,010
You said you're Detective Cha Soo Yeong, right?

241
00:19:13,010 --> 00:19:15,760
Your name was in his notebook as well.

242
00:19:17,460 --> 00:19:21,500
This looks like a case I was investigating.

243
00:19:21,500 --> 00:19:25,140
I had asked him about Chim Sa Bong.

244
00:19:25,140 --> 00:19:30,260
Did he look into Chim Sa Bong by any chance?

245
00:19:30,260 --> 00:19:31,910
I'm not sure about that.

246
00:19:31,910 --> 00:19:36,190
Only he would know the contents of his notebook.

247
00:19:37,590 --> 00:19:42,510
Could I maybe see his case file?

248
00:19:47,760 --> 00:19:49,610
Hello, Team Leader?

249
00:19:50,360 --> 00:19:54,040
Yes. Okay.

250
00:20:02,920 --> 00:20:04,760

251
00:20:04,760 --> 00:20:09,190

252
00:20:09,190 --> 00:20:10,980
Goodbye.

253
00:20:17,300 --> 00:20:18,480
Hello?

254
00:20:18,480 --> 00:20:19,750
 Sunbae, it's me.

255
00:20:19,750 --> 00:20:21,870
You know that Section Chief Bang died, right?

256
00:20:21,870 --> 00:20:24,080
Of course, I do. I saw him in person.

257
00:20:24,080 --> 00:20:26,040
The news already spread that far?

258
00:20:26,040 --> 00:20:28,180
I'm at Hwayeong Police Station.

259
00:20:28,180 --> 00:20:31,500
He called me before that happened.

260
00:20:31,500 --> 00:20:33,730
He did? To you? Why?

261
00:20:33,730 --> 00:20:36,300
I had made a request before.

262
00:20:36,300 --> 00:20:39,920
I was the last one he spoke to, so I'm here to give a witness statement.

263
00:20:39,920 --> 00:20:41,470
What did you request?

264
00:20:41,470 --> 00:20:43,190
 There's something.

265
00:20:43,190 --> 00:20:48,830
Sunbae, was there anything odd about him lately?

266
00:20:48,830 --> 00:20:53,240
There are rumors that he was gambling and that he got private loans.

267
00:20:53,240 --> 00:20:55,590
These rumors were going around.

268
00:20:55,590 --> 00:20:58,900
 You're at Hwayeong Police Station? You want me to come get you?

269
00:20:58,900 --> 00:21:02,800
No. I'll call you later.

270
00:21:05,210 --> 00:21:07,430
Gambling and private loans?

271
00:21:08,350 --> 00:21:10,220
Private loans...

272
00:21:10,800 --> 00:21:14,220
Gambling, unregistered car...

273
00:21:15,120 --> 00:21:18,140
Ah, whom can I ask?

274
00:21:26,600 --> 00:21:27,890
Gosh, you scared me!

275
00:21:27,890 --> 00:21:29,940
